[INAUDIBLE].

00:43:22.604 --> 00:43:23.530
NILOFER MERCHANT: Yeah.

00:43:23.530 --> 00:43:26.410
So one of the things that they
actually just said in the

00:43:26.410 --> 00:43:27.320
interview process--

00:43:27.320 --> 00:43:30.720
because I was trying to get this
article to be really as

00:43:30.720 --> 00:43:31.450
tight as possible.

00:43:31.450 --> 00:43:34.380
And so I asked them, how do
you think about this?

00:43:34.380 --> 00:43:36.990
How do you think about the
management part of this?

00:43:36.990 --> 00:43:37.610
And they said, listen.

00:43:37.610 --> 00:43:39.860
It's not us managing.

00:43:39.860 --> 00:43:43.160
It's not me going out there
and saying, no, no, no.

00:43:43.160 --> 00:43:45.850
It's figuring out how to raise
the bar and standard where

00:43:45.850 --> 00:43:48.760
they tell each other no.

00:43:48.760 --> 00:43:52.580
You should not have, you should
not be a TEDx licensee.

00:43:52.580 --> 00:43:54.070
Not that person.

00:43:54.070 --> 00:43:57.520
And it finds a way
to filter out.

00:43:57.520 --> 00:44:00.100
It's a very similar system to
what eBay created when the

00:44:00.100 --> 00:44:01.190
first transactions happened.

00:44:01.190 --> 00:44:04.610
How do you build more trust in
the system because social era

00:44:04.610 --> 00:44:06.230
is all about relationships.

00:44:06.230 --> 00:44:08.810
So relationships are the way
in which we're going to

00:44:08.810 --> 00:44:09.250
measure it.

00:44:09.250 --> 00:44:10.820
Trust is an outcome
of a relationship.

00:44:10.820 --> 00:44:12.310
How do you build up trust?

00:44:12.310 --> 00:44:14.720
So they've got to figure out how
to build more metrics into

00:44:14.720 --> 00:44:18.280
the system, feedback loop back
to TED saying these people did

00:44:18.280 --> 00:44:20.490
not put on a good event, et
cetera so the license does not

00:44:20.490 --> 00:44:20.920
get renewed.

00:44:20.920 --> 00:44:23.670
So the system becomes
reinforcing.

00:44:23.670 --> 00:44:25.590
And peer reviews end up
really shaping that.

00:44:25.590 --> 00:44:26.690
So there are ways to do it.

00:44:26.690 --> 00:44:29.860
But they have to think about
it not as them telling, or

00:44:29.860 --> 00:44:33.420
them directing, or them even
being in charge because the

00:44:33.420 --> 00:44:35.115
way to do a community is to
have a community police.

